Upstream bug: web-transport-quinn 0.11.8 passes the web-transport-trait stream
priority (u8, LOWER value = send first; moq-lite gives the newest group 0) to
quinn's SendStream::set_priority (i32, HIGHER value = send first) without
negating it. Under congestion this inverts MoQ's intended newest-first
scheduling into oldest-first FIFO, so latency accumulates without bound.

Apply inside a vendored copy of the crate (see patches/README.md):
  cp -r ~/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-*/web-transport-quinn-0.11.8 \
        external/moq/vendor/web-transport-quinn
  cd external/moq/vendor/web-transport-quinn && git apply <this file>
The vendored copy is wired in via [patch.crates-io] in the moq workspace
Cargo.toml (added by moq-send-stats.patch).

--- a/src/send.rs
+++ b/src/send.rs
@@ -148,7 +148,7 @@
     type Error = WriteError;

     fn set_priority(&mut self, order: u8) {
-        Self::set_priority(self, order.into()).ok();
+        Self::set_priority(self, -i32::from(order)).ok(); // PATCH: trait contract is lower-first, quinn is higher-first
     }

     fn reset(&mut self, code: u32) {
